    "For each of these models, the ICL variant showed modest improvements in generating contextually correct Py-Chrono scripts.",
    "While the gains were modest, so was the effort of creating the prompts.",
    "In general, in-context learning is recommended only in cases where the training data and/or computational resources are limited.",
    "Evaluation results for ICL demonstrate noticeable performance variations among different LLM architectures.",
    "Finally, the results for the SFT models show a significant improvement in performance over both the pre-trained and ICL models."
